  <hr />

  <!-- Assignment Timeline -->
  <h4 class="mb-2">üìö Assignment Timeline (1‚Äì7)</h4>
  <p class="text-muted">
    Click on each assignment to see what was added to BlazorForum during that step.
  </p>

  <div class="vstack gap-2 mb-4">

    <details class="border rounded p-2">
      <summary class="fw-semibold">Assignment 1 ‚Äì First Web API &amp; DTOs</summary>
      <div class="mt-2">
        <p>We built the very first version of the API using in-memory data:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Created <code>User</code>, <code>Post</code>, and <code>Comment</code> entities</li>
          <li>Introduced DTOs so the API never returns entities directly</li>
          <li>Exposed basic CRUD endpoints for users, posts, and comments</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="border rounded p-2">
      <summary class="fw-semibold">Assignment 2 ‚Äì Validation &amp; Global Error Handling</summary>
      <div class="mt-2">
        <p>We made the API more robust and user-friendly:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Input validation for usernames, passwords, titles, and bodies</li>
          <li>Custom exceptions like <code>NotFoundException</code> and <code>ValidationException</code></li>
          <li>Global exception middleware returning clean HTTP responses (400, 404, 500)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="border rounded p-2">
      <summary class="fw-semibold">Assignment 3 ‚Äì Repository Pattern &amp; File Storage</summary>
      <div class="mt-2">
        <p>We separated logic from data access using repositories:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Interfaces in <code>RepositoryContracts</code> (e.g. <code>IUserRepository</code>)</li>
          <li>File-based repositories in <code>FileRepositories</code> storing data in JSON files</li>
          <li>Controllers became storage-agnostic (clean architecture)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="border rounded p-2">
      <summary class="fw-semibold">Assignment 4 ‚Äì Web API Improvements &amp; Query Support</summary>
      <div class="mt-2">
        <p>We improved how clients can query and work with data:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Added query parameters like <code>?titleContains=</code> and <code>?authorUserId=</code></li>
          <li>More structured DTOs for create, update, and list / summary</li>
          <li>Better HTTP status codes (<code>201 Created</code>, <code>204 NoContent</code>)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="border rounded p-2">
      <summary class="fw-semibold">Assignment 5 ‚Äì Blazor Client (UI)</summary>
      <div class="mt-2">
        <p>We built the Blazor frontend that talks to the Web API via <code>HttpClient</code>:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Pages for Home/Feed, Posts, Comments, and Users</li>
          <li>Services like <code>IUserService</code>, <code>IPostService</code>, <code>ICommentService</code></li>
          <li>Forms for creating and editing posts and comments with validation messages</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="border rounded p-2">
      <summary class="fw-semibold">Assignment 6 ‚Äì Authentication &amp; ‚ÄúMy‚Äù Pages</summary>
      <div class="mt-2">
        <p>We added simple authentication and user-specific views:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Login endpoint in the API and a Blazor login page</li>
          <li>Custom <code>AuthenticationStateProvider</code> to store the logged-in user</li>
          <li><strong>‚ÄúMy posts‚Äù</strong> and <strong>‚ÄúMy comments‚Äù</strong> views filtered by the current user</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="border rounded p-2">
      <summary class="fw-semibold">Assignment 7 ‚Äì EF Core &amp; SQLite</summary>
      <div class="mt-2">
        <p>Finally, we replaced file storage with a real relational database:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Introduced <code>AppContext : DbContext</code> with <code>DbSet&lt;User&gt;</code>,
              <code>DbSet&lt;Post&gt;</code>, and <code>DbSet&lt;Comment&gt;</code></li>
          <li>Configured SQLite (<code>app.db</code>) and created migrations with <code>dotnet ef</code></li>
          <li>Added navigation properties and relationships (user ‚Üí posts/comments, post ‚Üí comments)</li>
          <li>Implemented <code>EfcUserRepository</code>, <code>EfcPostRepository</code>,
              <code>EfcCommentRepository</code> and wired them via DI</li>
          <li>Used <code>Include</code> / <code>ThenInclude</code> to load posts together with authors and comments</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

  </div>

  <hr />

  <!-- Learning -->
